ARTICLE.TITLE: Hurricane Dorian: Will my postal delivery be suspended?
ARTICLE.TEXT:
The U.S. Postal Service has announced the temporary suspension of delivery and retail operations because of Hurricane Dorian.

Delivery will be suspended in South Florida ZIP codes beginning with 334 and 349 on Tuesday.

More:Uber suspends free rides, cites deteriorating weather conditions

More:Bridges in Indian River will close at midnight; Martin, St. Lucie already closed

Customers from Pompano Beach south through Key West (ZIP codes beginning with 330, 331, 332 and 333) may continue to conduct business transactions at their local post office and will receive regular mail delivery.
